        <div>
            <h1 class="syntax_textcolor">C# Comments</h1>
            <p><b>Comments</b> can be used to explain C# code, and to make it more readable. </p>
            <p>It can also be used to prevent execution when testing alternative code.</p><br /><br /><hr />

            <h1 class="syntax_textcolor">Types of Comments : </h1>
            <ul>
                <li>1) Single Line Comment - //</li>
                <li>2) Multi Line Comment - /*  */</li>
            </ul><br /><br /><hr />

            <h2 class="syntax_textcolor">1) Single Line comment - //</h2>
            <p>Any text between // and the end of the line is ignored by C# (will not be executed).</p><br /><br /><hr />

            <h2 class="syntax_textcolor">2) MultiLine Comment - /*  */</h2>
            <p><b>Multi-line comments</b> start with /* and ends with */.</p>
            <p>Any text between /* and */ will be ignored by C#.</p><br /><br /><hr />
        </div>
